race.comment: Another even race. TROPICAL SUN (4) doesn't win out of turn but has been super consistent lately. Runner-up two back at Bunbury the  came from last here last time and finished fifth. Extra trip a plus and looks hard to hold out. PENNED (10) raced in the same race as TROPICAL SUN last time and weakened late after sitting three deep for the trip. Slightly better drawn this time and can do much better. SECRICITY (11) charged home here over 1400m last time and beat a few of these home. Among the leading chances back to six furlongs. NORTHERN IVY (9) was in the same race and finished sixth. Placed 2/3 course and distance and should be prominent off the low draw. DOTHRAKI (2) was another from that race and finished seventh. Shorter trip suits and can do much better.
